race.comment: SHE'S CAPITANA (9) led them up on debut over the 1100m journey here but couldn't hold on late, beaten 2L at the finish. Back to 1000m today doesn't seem an issue and it sets up nicely for her down in the weights from an inside alley. Pike sticks and she looks set to go one better now. LONG LAUGH (2) stuck on well over 1200m last start at Belmont to finish only 0.6L off the winner. Back in trip today off a 32-day freshen, she'll need a touch of luck from the draw but she showed last start she's good enough to be winning a race of this calibre. Can land the knockout blow. COUNTRY EDITION (11) has impressed at the trials under Dhurun coming into this race and creates plenty of interest. Two of her 3 siblings are race winners and she maps to get her chance. Right in the mix. DANCEWITHME (6) pulled up with an issue first-up. Happy to forgive that effort and she's expected to bounce back. APACHE ADIOS (5) gets a few gear changes today and that can see her improve.
